text: Faysal Ahmed is a Somali-American actor from Minneapolis, Minnesota. He was born in Mogadishu, Somalia in 1985. He was raised in Yemen in his childhood and at the age of 14 his family settled in USA. He is most known for his role in the 2013 movie "Captain Phillips", where he played Najee. ==References== Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:Actors from Minnesota Category:People from Mogadishu Category:African actors
